1. The `fetchTeltonikaIoData` method connects to the specified URL and retrieves the HTML document.
2. It then extracts the body element of the document.
3. The `body.text()` method is used to get the text content of the body element, which includes all the text within the body of the HTML document.
4. If an exception occurs, the error message is returned.
5. The `main` method is added to demonstrate how to use the `ScrapeTeltonikaPage` class and print the scraped data.

You can run this code to see the scraped data from the specified website.
