To return the data line by line, you can use the `body.html()` method to get the HTML content of the body element and then split it by line breaks. Here is the updated code to achieve that:

```java
package com.xenya52.fmc003_rest_api.service;

import org.jsoup.Jsoup;
import org.jsoup.nodes.Document;
import org.jsoup.nodes.Element;
import org.jsoup.select.Elements;

public class ScrapeTeltonikaPage {

    private String teltonikaIoData;

    public ScrapeTeltonikaPage() {
        this.teltonikaIoData = fetchTeltonikaIoData();
    }

    public String getIoData() {
        return teltonikaIoData;
    }

    // Get data from TeltonikaIo
    private String fetchTeltonikaIoData() {
        try {
            Document doc = Jsoup.connect(
                "https://wiki.teltonika-gps.com/view/FMC003_Teltonika_Data_Sending_Parameters_ID"
            ).get();
            Element body = doc.body();
            StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
            for (Element element : body.children()) {
                sb.append(element.text()).append("\n");
            }
            return sb.toString();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return e.getMessage();
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ScrapeTeltonikaPage scraper = new ScrapeTeltonikaPage();
        System.out.println(scraper.getIoData());
    }
}
```

In this code:
1. The `fetchTeltonikaIoData` method connects to the specified URL and retrieves the HTML document.
2. It then extracts the body element of the document.
3. A `StringBuilder` is used to accumulate the text content of each child element of the body, appending a newline character after each element's text.
4. The `body.children()` method is used to get all the direct child elements of the body.
5. The `element.text()` method is used to get the text content of each child element.
6. The accumulated text is returned as a single string with each line separated by a newline character.
7. If an exception occurs, the error message is returned.
8. The `main` method is added to demonstrate how to use the `ScrapeTeltonikaPage` class and print the scraped data.

